<HEADLINE> (Update with more info) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of the Security
and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) announced on Thursday that it has
decided to extend the deadline of in-country voter registration
for Bosnia's local elections.
</P>
<P>
The extension of the deadline from June 16 to June 28 was aimed
at allowing more voters inside Bosnia to register, according to
David Foley, a spokesman for OSCE. The deadline for out-of-country
voter registration remains on June 14.
</P>
<P>
Foley said that out of estimated 3.5 million eligible voters,
only 1.8 million have registered, including both people inside
Bosnia and refugees abroad.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian local elections, arranged by OSCE, will be held in
September and the race is participated by more than 100 parties.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, OSCE Provision Election Commission, which is
in charge of the local elections, announced that it has demanded
the removal of presidents of the Brcko election commission and of
voter registration centers there for pervasive violation of
registration rules.
</P>
<P>
OSCE said that cases of violation such as providing false
documents and bringing refugees from outside have been found in
Brcko that the voters were forced to close down on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Foley said that a new voter registration for Brcko will start
on June 18 and last until July 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
