<HEADLINE> Chinese CPPCC Leader's Europe Tour A Success: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
Li Ruihuan's visit to Portugal, Greece and Germany has been a
great success and has greatly promoted China's ties with the three
countries, a Chinese official accompanying Li during his visit
said on their way home today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Xun, the CPPCC's secretary-general, said Li's Europe
tour, which lasted from May 26 to June 11, was made at the
invitation of the Portuguese, Greek parliaments and the German
government. The three countries attached much importance to Li's
visit and granted him a warm welcome.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said Li told his hosts he had attached much importance to
China's exchanges and cooperation with the three nations in
political, economic and cultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
Li said China is ready to make concerted efforts with the three
countries to continue to develop their friendly, long-term
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed heartfelt thanks, on behalf of the Chinese
government and its people, to the Greek government for helping
Chinese nationals in Albania withdraw from the country in
March.
</P>
<P>
The three nations think highly of China's reform policies and
its outstanding economic achievements and will follow China's
future development with great interest, Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China will stick to the late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics. This is because the theory, representing the
people's interests and desires and having permeated into China's
political, economic and cultural sectors, has proved correct.
</P>
<P>
Li said the third-generation leadership of the Central
Committee of Chinese Communist Party, with Jiang Zemin at the
core, is a powerful unity loyal to Deng's theory and therefore is
totally capable of pushing even further China's reforms and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
There are three things essential to present-day China, Li
said. First, to stick to Deng's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics. Second, to maintain social stability and
order. Third, to resolve knotty economic and social problems
without delay. The Chinese people are confident that they will
step into the new century together with a more vigorous China.




nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
