<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Car Industry Reports Surge in Domestic Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany car industry today reported a
19 percent surge in domestic orders in May, but only a two percent
slight increase in foreign demand.
</P>
<P>
According to the Frankfurt-based German Automobile Industry
Association VDI, Germany's production of all types of vehicles was
400,300 in May, down five percent from May last year. Adjusting
for the fewer working days in May this year, production was about
at the same level compared with the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
For the first five months of 1997, Germany has produced 2.13
million vehicles, unchanged from the level of the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Germany's car exports in the first five months were 1.28
million, up five percent over the same period of 1996, while
domestic sales dropped five percent to 1.62 million, the VDI said.
</P>
</TEXT>
