<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese CPPCC Leader's Europe Tour A Success: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu Xun said that during his visit, Li explained China's
principled stance on civilization and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Li said countries with different cultural backgrounds should
respect and learn from each other and keep their own cultural
characters. Only when these principles are observed can human
society achieve peace and stability, diversity and progress.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with German leaders and reporters, Li elaborated
on China's basic views on human rights: the universally accepted
principles on human rights should be respected; they should be
combined with different situations in different countries; the
realization of the principles was a gradual process.
</P>
<P>
He said all countries should improve the development in the
cause of human rights through exchanges and dialogues on an equal
footing.
</P>
<P>
Some people were over-confident about their countries' human
rights conditions and made unwarranted charges against other
countries, especially the developing nations. This was by no means
helpful to the realization of the universally accepted principles.
</P>
<P>
Li's remarks drew much attention from the three countries'
leaderships and the media there.
</P>
<P>
Li praised those leaders' foresight and sagacity reflected in
developing bilateral relations with China and in other
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said that a state leader, especially of an influential
country in the world, shoulders important historic responsibility
and should, therefore, be responsible for his words, actions and
decisions, and contribute more to the human society.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said there are some people in the world who spread the
rumor of "China Threat" with evil intentions. Li refuted the
rumor by calling it sheer fabrication.
</P>
<P>
Li said China had suffered a lot from foreign imperialist
aggressions and humiliations and paid a heavy price in blood in
resistance.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the Chinese people hate and oppose hegemonism and
will never harm other countries by practicing it.
</P>
<P>
China is still a developing country with a rather backward
economy and culture. China will not bully and threaten others even
if it becomes strong and prosperous someday, he continued.
</P>
<P>
Li said the "China threat" is nothing but a pretext fabricated
by a handful of people who hate to see China continue to progress
on the road it chose for itself, for fear that a powerful China
would hinder their own practice of hegemonism.
</P>
<P>
When explaining China's foreign policy, Li stressed on more
than one occasion that "China's own conditions have determined
that we must create a friendly and peaceful international
environment in order to concentrate on developing the economy,
improving people's living standards, cooperating with other
countries and learning from others' experiences."
</P>
<P>
"We do not want to have brushes or contradictions with any
other nation. The progress of China, with a population of 1.2
billion, is in itself a great contribution to the international
community."
</P>
<P>
Li also told the leaders of the three countries about the
transition of Hong Kong and Deng's great concept of "one country,
two systems" for resolving the Taiwan, Kong Kong and Macao issues.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese leaders expressed confidence in continuing close
cooperation with China to achieve Macao's smooth return to China.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the three countries said they are confident Hong
Kong will remain stable and prosperous after its return.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed them about the makeup and basic functions of
the CPPCC as well as the construction of China's socialist
democracy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
