<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Gets 500m Dollar Investment in Power Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- With the initialing of the fourth
power purchase agreement today, Bangladesh has attracted around
500 million U.S. dollars of private investment from abroad for the
power sector.
</P>
<P>
The fourth 15-year agreement for power generation was initialed
in Dhaka today between the Bangladesh Power Development Board
(PDB) and Westmont Offshore, Malaysia, said a press release issued
by the PDB.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Westmont Offshore will install and
commission a 100 megawatt (MW) capacity barge-mounted plant at
Khulna and supply electricity to PDB within 10 months of signing
the agreement on a Built-Own-Operate basis.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, three separate agreements for private sector power
generation were initialed in May and June for installation and
commissioning of three barge-mounted power plants of 100 MW
capacity each at Haripur, Sikalbaha and Khulna city respectively.
</P>
<P>
To solve the long-standing power crisis throughout the country,
the Bangladeshi government last October changed its policy and
allowed power generation by the private sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
