<HEADLINE> India's Ruling Front Reacts Cautiously to Kesri's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- India's ruling United Front
today reacted cautiously to the election of Sitaram Kesri as
president of the Congress party which provides the vital support
to the coalition government from the outside, Press Trust of India
(PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
Kesri, the incumbent president of the Congress party, was
re-elected after defeating two rivals in a poll held on June 9.
The result of balloting was announced today after the counting of
votes here.
</P>
<P>
A senior minister in the United Front government declined to
comment saying it was an "internal affairs of a friendly party,"
according to PTI.
</P>
<P>
Sharad Yadav, working president of the Janata Dal, felt that
there was no immediate threat to the United Front government on
the election of Kesri who had withdrawn support from the
government headed by H.D. Deve Gowda on March 30.
</P>
<P>
The Janata Dal is the largest constituent of the 16-party
United Front. 
</P>
