<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Regrets at Fighting in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today expressed regret at continued fighting and
bloodshed in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Turkmen Foreign Minister Boris Shikhmyradov
who arrived here today for a visit to Iran, Rafsanjani said that
military confrontation is not the solution to the Afghan crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The infighting should be brought to an end through
negotiations and respect for the interests of the Afghan
people," he was quoted by the official news agency IRNA as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Afghanistan's Taliban militia, in control of most
the country since last year, launched a large-scale offensive
in the north against opposition forces.
</P>
<P>
According to the IRNA report, the Iranian president also
welcomed expansion of bilateral cooperation between Iran and
Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani mentioned the positive outcomes of trilateral
cooperation among Iran, Turkmenistan and Armenia, saying that it
is useful to foster regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Shikhmyradov said that Iran and Turkmenistan have expanded
cooperation in the region and there is no problem in this
respect.
</P>
<P>
He said Turkmenistan believes that ending civil war in
Afghanistan was a prerequisite for return of peace and security
in that country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
