<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's National Association for Blind Calls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's National
Association for the Blind today called for job opportunity for
blind women.
</P>
<P>
The call came from Tesfanish Beyene, secretary of women's
affair section in the association at a ceremony here to hand- out
certificates to 20 blind women who attended a five-month training
in knitting and other vocations.
</P>
<P>
She noted that 60 blind women trained over the last three
months couldn't get job despite their efficient performance.
</P>
<P>
"The life of these blind women could go even more sour if they
are not given job opportunity in the respective trades they were
trained," she said.
</P>
<P>
She urged pertinent governmental and non-governmental
organizations to address the problem and strive to make blind
women self-reliant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
