<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Remain Prosperous: Mrs. Chennault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The concept of "one country,
two systems" will guarantee sustained prosperity and stability for
Hong Kong after July 1, said Anna Chennault, chairman of the
Council for International Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, Mrs. Chennault, widow of
late General Claire Lee Chennault who led the U.S. Air Force
commandos of Flying Tiger against the Japanese invaders in China
during the World War II, expressed her optimism about the future
of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The concept of "one country, two systems," proposed by late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, is "a great innovation" and will go
down in history, Mrs. Chennault said.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Chennault, who returned here from Hong Kong two months ago,
said that she was deeply impressed by the patriotism of the people
in Hong Kong during her five-month stay there.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong people, from ordinary citizens to business
leaders, have been actively participating in patriotic
activities," she said. "With Hong Kong's return to the embrace of
the motherland, they will become the masters of Hong Kong. So they
are more confident that they can build Hong Kong into a better
place."
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Chennault also noted that the smooth transition and
sustained economic prosperity and development of Hong Kong would
be a model for the peaceful reunification of the motherland with
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
She said she believes that the differences between the two
sides of the Taiwan Strait will be narrowed through further
negotiations, if they follow the Hong Kong model.
</P>
<P>
People on either side of the Taiwan Strait are Chinese, and
"the issues of the Chinese people should be resolved by
themselves," she stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
