<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is planning to
close five of its border posts with land-locked neighboring
Swaziland as part of the drive to combat cross-border crime.
</P>
<P>
South African Customs Union spokesman Christo Henning said in
Mbabane, capital of Swaziland, that the planned closures formed
part of a national exercise to scale down the number of exit and
entry points into South Africa, reported the African Eye News
Service.
</P>
<P>
The closure was also part of South Africa's national crime
prevention strategy and was aimed at reducing the influx of
smuggled and fake goods, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Only six of the current 11 border posts with Swaziland would
be retained. Some of the border posts expected to be closed were
still operating but would be phased out before the end of the
year. 
