<HEADLINE> Mary Robinson Appointed High Commissioner for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Thursday appointed former Irish President Mary Robinson
as the High Commissioner for Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the appointment, Annan said he expected Mary
Robinson to take office before the fifty-second session of the
General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
The post of the High Commissioner for Refugees was set up in
December 1993. He (or She) is the U.N. official with principal
responsibility for U.N. human rights activities. Under relevant
General Assembly resolution, there is a fixed term of four years
with the possibility of a further term of four years.
</P>
<P>
The first High Commissioner, Jose Ayala-Lasso of Ecuador, took
office in April 1994. But he submitted resignation in March
because he have appointed as the foreign minister of Ecuador.
</P>
</TEXT>
