<HEADLINE> S.Africa's Sugar Giant to Be Listed on Swazi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 12 (Xinhau) -- South Africa's sugar giant
Illovo Sugar announced today in Mbabane, capital of Swaziland,
that it would be soon listed on the Swaziland Stock Exchange,
reported African Eye News Service.
</P>
<P>
The announcement followed shortly after Illovo acquired the
majority stake in Swaziland's Ubombo Ranches Sugar Company, which
planned to diversify its product range by concentrating on sugar
based by-products, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Illovo said the planned stock exchange listing and
consolidation with Ubombo would give additional impetus to
Illovo's plans to increase support for more small-holder sugar
cane growing schemes to boost production at their plant in the
southeast region of the kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
