<HEADLINE> Arab National Liberation Movements Protest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the
Damascus-based Arab national liberation movements and friendly
forces submitted a protest today against Turkish incursion into
northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The representatives organized a sit-in strike in front of the
Turkish Embassy premises here, denouncing the ongoing Turkish
military operation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
A statement signed by 23 parties, organizations, political
movements and leagues, both Arab and friendly ones, condemned the
Turkish incursion into northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The statement described the incursion as a flagrant violation
of Iraq's sovereignty and territorial integrity in contradiction
with international laws.
</P>
<P>
The statement called upon the Turkish government to order the
unconditional withdrawal of Turkish troops from Iraqi territory,
and to reconsider its alliance with Israel.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 Turkish troop poured into northern Iraq on May 14
to attack bases of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
which were used for raids into southeast Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
