<HEADLINE> Fabius Elected French Parliament Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Laurent Fabius, a former Socialist
prime minister under President Francois Mitterrand, was elected
today the speaker of the new French National Assembly, or lower
house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
Fabius won 292 votes from a poll joined by 535 members of
parliament who cast 518 valid votes, beating Nicole Catala of the
Gaullist Rally for the Republic, who won 223 votes.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time for Fabius to serve as parliament
speaker, a post he occupied from 1988 to 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
