<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Endorses Designation of New Bosnia High Represensative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council
today endorsed the designation of Carlos Westendorp from Spain to
succeed Carl Bildt as High Representative to Bosnia and
Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
In adopting the resolution, the Security Council reaffirmed the
importance it attached to the role of the High Representative on
monitoring the implementation of the Peace Agreement and giving
guidance to and coordinating the activities of the civilian
organizations and agencies involved in assisting the parties to
implement the Peace Agreement.
</P>
<P>
It also stressed that the High Representative was the final
authority regarding the interpretation on civilian implementation
of the Peace Agreement and that in case of dispute he might give
his interpretation and make his recommendations.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council welcomed the conclusion of the Ministerial
Meeting of the Steering Board of the Peace Implementation Council
held in Sintra, Portugal, on May 30, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
