<HEADLINE> European Shares Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended higher today.
</P>
<P>
On the London market, British shares notched up another closing
high, encouraged by much weaker-than-expected economic data from
the United States which spurred the Dow into record ground. The
FTSE-100 closed at 4,757.4, up 32.6 points, or 0.69 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, Germany's IBIS DAX index rallied to end
electronic trade at a new all-time closing high, having made a new
record high of 3,739.28 points late in the day. The DAX-30 index
closed at 3,707.99, up 30.56 points.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the Paris market also closed sharply higher. The
CAC-40 index closed at 2,760.27, up 64.08 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
