<HEADLINE> Communist Party Departments Checks Extravagance and Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Departments and Institutions under
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee have been
making conscientious efforts to check extravagance and waste.
</P>
<P>
Several days ago, the Work Committee of the Departments under
the CPC Central Committee issued a notice calling on the central
departments and institutions to carry out the regulations of the
CPC Central Committee and the State Council stipulating that
extravagance be stopped.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the notice, the departments and institutions have
worked out detailed measures, such as halting constructing or
buying office buildings, reducing the number of meetings and
ceremonies, suspending the practice of elaborately decorating
offices, and checking the excessive use of public telephones and
cars by individuals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
