<HEADLINE> Basuki into Classic Tennis Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Yayuk Basuki advanced
to the semifinals of the DFS Classic women's grass-court
tournament Friday after beating Magdalena Maleeva 7-6 (7-4), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Basuki, the No. 4 seed, wound up her victory over the
seventh-seeded Bulgarian just before rain suspended play in the
other quarterfinal matches.
</P>
<P>
Two other quarterfinals were suspended at one set all when the
rain came again.
</P>
<P>
Nathalie Tauziat, the No. 2 seed from France, won the first set
6-1 against No. 8 Natasha Zvereva of Belarus, who took the second
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Australian qualifier Kristine Kunce had the chance of a match
point against third-seeded Lisa Raymond of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Kunce took the first set 6-4 and had reached 6-6 in the
second-set tiebreaker when a stray ball from the next court forced
umRaymond won it and went on to take the tiebreaker 9-7.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Irina Spirlea, the top seed, was due to face No. 6
Dominique Van Roost of Belgium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
