<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stable Grain Market in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- China's grain supply has basically
caught up with its demand so far this year, leading to a stable
grain market nationwide, according to the China Price Information
Center.
</P>
<P>
Grain output in Chine hit a record 480 billion kg last year,
giving a boost to grain in stock.
</P>
<P>
The country's demand for feed grain and that for industrial use
has climbed in recent years, compared with the slight drop in the
citizens' demand for grain.
</P>
<P>
The average annual consumption of grain per capita went down
from 130 kg in 1990 to 97 kg in 1995 in the country's urban areas,
and from 262 kg to 259 kg in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
These have led to a stable grain price in the country, the
center said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
