<HEADLINE> 28 Killed in Cinema Fire in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 28 people were killed
and nearly 200 injured when a major fire broke out in a packed
cinema in downtown New Delhi this evening, the Press Trust of
India reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at 17:10 hours local time when the cinema in
south Delhi with a capacity of 1,400 was showing a latest domestic
film.
</P>
<P>
Of the 76 people who were brought to two nearby hospitals, 27
were declared dead upon arrival while another one succumbed to
injuries in one of the hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations are still under way. But the cause of the
fire remains unknown.  
</P>
</TEXT>
