<HEADLINE> Pak Inflation Rate Projected to Be at 12 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's inflation rate during
1997-98 fiscal year has been projected to be at around 12 percent
as compared to 10.8 percent in 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
According to the national budget for 1997-98 presented by the
government here today, prices remained under pressure in 1996-97
mainly due to the reduction of agricultural and industrial
production, high prices of import products and increase in utility
prices.
</P>
<P>
During the first 10 months of the current financial year,
Sensitive Price Index, Consume Price Index and Wholesale Price
Index increased by 13.3 percent, 13.0 percent and 12.1 percent
respectively over the same period of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
