<P>
PARIS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Jens Heppner won the fifth
stage of the Criterium du Dauphine cycling race on Friday, a 169km
leg from Cavaillon to Digne-les-bains in France, while Russia's
Viacheslav Ekimov kept the overall leader's yellow jersey.
