<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Customs See Booming Foreign Trade from January to May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from China's customs
show that from January to May this year, the total volume of
foreign trade reached 117.04 billion US dollars, a rise of 12.5
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The volume of export was 65.48 billion US dollars, increasing
by 26.4 percent over last year, while the import volume decreased
1.2 percent to 51.56 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Over the five months, the monthly increase rates of export all
exceeded 20 percent. And the accumulated favorable balance of
foreign trade was 13.92 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The export volume of China's state-owned enterprises rose by 25
percent over last year and claimed 56 percent of the total export
volume.
</P>
<P>
The export volume of overseas-funded firms rose by 26.5 percent
and took up 41 percent of the total export volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Several Feared Dead in Delhi Blaze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Several people were feared
killed and scores injured in a major fire that raged through a
packed cinema hall in downtown area of the Indian capital this
evening, the Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters and police personnel were busy rescuing people
still trapped inside the blazing cinema hall located in south
Delhi.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out around 17:00 hours local time when the
cinema hall with a capacity of 1,400 was showing a latest domestic
film.
</P>
<P>
According to fire brigade officials, 60 of about 160 people
rescued so far were taken to various hospitals in unconscious
condition.
</P>
<P>
The entire area has been cordoned off and scores of fire
tenders and ambulances have been summoned from across the capital
to control the blaze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
