<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Aerospace Pioneer Zhang Jun Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Jun, one of the pioneers of
China's aerospace industry, died of illness in Beijing on June
2. He was 78.
</P>
<P>
Zhang devoted nearly 40 years to the country's aerospace
industry. He was a former minister of the Aerospace Industry and a
Standing Committee member of the Seventh National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing,
Hu Jintao, and other officials expressed their condolences to
Zhang's family.
</P>
<P>
A native of Shandong Province in east China, Zhang joined
revolutionary work in 1935 and became a Communist Party member in
1937.
</P>
<P>
Since the late 1950s, Zhang had been engaged in research on
modern national defense, and later took part in the development of
missiles, rockets and satellites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
