<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Law Reiterated On Foreign Investment In Mining Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council recently issued a circular ordering local governments and
departments under the central government to abide by the laws and
regulations on foreign investment in the country's mining industry.
</P>
<P>
The circular praises foreign financers for their increasingly
bigger role in the inspection and exploration of mineral resources
in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, it says, some local government departments have
neglected to abide by related laws and procedures in approving the
foreign funding.
</P>
<P>
Localities must re-examine all local mining projects involving
overseas investment within three months after the document's date
of publication, June 6, it says.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the circular reiterates that only state-owned
petroleum and gas companies are authorized to cooperate with
foreign investors to invest in the mining sector, and local
governments and their departments have no right to deal with oil-
and gas-mining projects using foreign funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
