<HEADLINE> Nigerian Capital Supports Cash Crop Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Federal Capital Territory
(FCT), where the Nigerian capital is located, is to distribute 24
tons of assorted cash crop seeds to about 36,600 farmers this
farming season through its agricultural development project
(ADP).
</P>
<P>
At present, enough chemicals to cover about 150 hectares of
land have been acquired while arrangements have been concluded to
provide sufficient tractor services to back up the cash crop
production efforts, according to ADP Project Manager Bamiro
Obamiro.
</P>
<P>
Assigned the sole production of cashew in exportable quality,
the FCT ADP has already taken the challenge by establishing 15
cashew farms in the nine development centers of the territory.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ADP has also introduced cotton, wheat and
cowpea to the farmers, Obamiro said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, non-cash crops will be made available to the
farmers with the seeds of about 5.5 tons of maize, 13 tons of
rice and six tons of soybeans to be distributed to farmers this
farming season.
</P>
<P>
The ADP is also involved in livestocks, fishery and piggery
production in commercial quantities.  
</P>
