<HEADLINE> Wall Street Drives Australian Stocks To Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Consecutive record days on Wall
street have flowed through to market confidence in Australia with
the share market closing at a record high.
</P>
<P>
"Realistically the reason is the flow on from New York. New
York had five straight record days and we are just confident
against that," Reynolds Co. broker Peter Struk said.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 17.2 points up at 2655.3,
slightly down on its intraday high of 2656.2 in early afternoon
trading.
</P>
