and the all industrials index was up 24 points to 4162.0.
</P>
<P>
BHP gained 19 cents, while Rio Tinto climbed 30.6 cents.
</P>
<P>
In the media sector, profit-taking forced down News Corp shares
13 cents and its preferred shares lost 18 cents.
</P>
<P>
The food sector index was pushed 213.2 points higher to 6606.9,
with Coca-Cola Amatil leading the drive, which was up 34.9 cents.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 502.44 million shares worth 1154.31
million Australian dollars (869.20 million US dollars). 
