<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Garment Exports Up 9.5 Percent in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' earnings from
garment and textile exports reached 1.18 billion U.S. dollars in
May, up 9.5 percent from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Data released today by the Garments and Textile Export Board
showed purchases of apparel and non-apparel items by both quota
and non-quota countries increased during the month.
</P>
<P>
The United States led the quota countries by buying 911.4
million U.S. dollars worth of garment and textile from the
Philippines. It was followed by European countries and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Among non-quota countries, Japan and United Arab Emirates
remained the biggest buyers, with receipts amounting to 78.9
million U.S. dollars and 39.5 million U.S. dollars respectively,
the data said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
