<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Leader Meets Russian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese people would like to
see a prosperous Russia where the people live happily, Li Ruihuan,
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) said here today during a
meeting with Chairman of the International Affairs Committee of
Russia's Federation Council Prusak Mikhail Mikhailovich.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia are each other's biggest neighbors, and the
Chinese people cherish special feelings towards the Russian
people, Li pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said the development and prosperity of China and Russia,
their good-neighborliness and mutually beneficial cooperation are
not only in the fundamental interests of the two countries and
their peoples, but are also significant to the peace and stability
of the Asia-Pacific and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
In the last few years, Li said, the exchange of high-level
visits between China and Russia have done much to improve the
overall development of the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC and Russia's Federation Council have a good
relationship, and so do the special committees under them, Li
said. "We hope the two sides will intensify the cooperation and
increase the mutual understanding and friendship," he added.
</P>
<P>
Prusak said in the good discussions between his delegation and
the Chinese friends, both sides expressed the hope that Russia's
Federation Council and CPPCC, and also the two countries will work
to maintain and develop their friendship.
</P>
<P>
The International Affairs Committee of Russia's Federation
Council will do its best to reach this end, Prusak stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Russian delegation arrived in Beijing Thursday on a
goodwill visit at the invitation of the Subcommittee of Foreign
Affairs of the CPPCC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
