<HEADLINE> Ramos Urges All Qualified Voters to Register </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today called on all qualified Filipinos to go out on Saturday and
register for the May 1998 national elections.
</P>
<P>
All Filipinos of voting age must register "as concerned
citizens of the country who are qualified voters" in their
respective registration centers, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Commission on Elections has set two weekends -- June 14 and
15 and May 21 and 22 -- for the general registration of voters.
President Ramos also released 300 million pesos (11.4 million U.S.
dollars) for the registration.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said he and the first lady will register Saturday morning
in his hometown in Pangasinan province, the northern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, the country's Supreme Court upheld its ban
on a charter change campaign, dimming hopes that President Ramos
could seek a second term by amending the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
According to the Constitution, Ramos should step down as his
term ends in June in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
