<HEADLINE> Australia Beats Tahiti 5-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 13 (Xinhua -- Australia whitewashed Tahiti 5-0
in an Oceania World Cup football qualifier in Sydney Friday.
</P>
<P>
Paul Trimboli scored twice in a five-minute period for the home
team in the first half with other goals coming from midfielder
Aurelio Vidmar, Hiroshima Sanfrecce striker Graham Arnold and
 Matthew Bingley.
</P>
<P>
The Australians led 3-0 at half-time.
</P>
<P>
The team swamped the Solomon Islands 13-0 here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Solomon Islands play Tahiti here on Sunday in the next match in
the group with the winner likely to play New Zealand over two
legs next month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
