<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Launches Annual Check-up of Extra-budgetary Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The check-up of extra-budgetary funds will start this month,
according to the notice, which was jointly issued by the Ministry
of Finance, the State Planning Commission, the State Auditing
Administration, the People's Bank of China and the Ministry of
Supervision.
</P>
<P>
Great success made in last year's effort to check up
extra-budgetary funds has effectively stopped a trend of illegally
setting up funds, increasing the number of fees and charges and
recklessly collecting and spending money, the notice said.
</P>
<P>
But problems connected with extra-budgetary funds have
accumulated over a long period of time, and some of them have not
been completely corrected, it noted.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are still areas that the previous review
failed to reach, the notice said.
</P>
<P>
This year's examination of extra-budgetary funds will focus
primarily on units in the police system, in industrial and
commercial administration and in the system for civil affair
administration, according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
In some places, the work to check up extra-budgetary funds has
already begun, it said, adding that the five government
departments will send special work teams to some areas or
departments to guide the check-up effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
