<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed at
its highs for the day against the US dollar, after silence from
the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) this morning on interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 75.30 US cents, up from 75.18 at
yesterday's close.
</P>
<P>
Derek Price, foreign exchange manager of the National Australia
Bank, said this afternoon's trade had seen dealers squaring their
positions ahead of the weekend and the beginning of trade in
London.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday's release of Australian Bureau of Statistics reported
a startling 40,300 fall in employment in the month of May and the
news has heightened speculation the RBA will further ease monetary
policy.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed firmer against the Japanese yen,
it was at 86.05 from 85.69 yesterday, and at 1.3018 from 1.2944
against the German mark.  
</P>
</TEXT>
