<HEADLINE> Forum Calls for More Western Aid for Africa (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bangkok Statement also said that special attention must be
paid to the role and needs of women, the transfer of technologies
including biotechnologies, water resources management programs and
technical cooperation programs and investment in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
At the forum, Chinese representative Li Guoqing, who is deputy
director general of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, said that during the last four decades, China has
provided various kinds of official assistance to Africa. The most
significant one was the 1,860-km-long Tanzania-Zambia Railway.
</P>
<P>
China's assistance to African countries covers a wide range of
sectors, including agriculture, animal husbandry, fishery, textile
industry, energy, road and transportation, broadcast and
telecommunications, irrigation and electric power,
machine-building, public and civil works, public health and
education, handcraft as well as food processing, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The forum was attended by senior officials from 44 African
countries, 11 Asian countries, 12 donor countries and 10
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The first Asia-Africa Forum was held in December 1994 in
Indonesia. The date and venue for the next one is yet to be fixed.
</P>
