<HEADLINE> Tung Welcomes India's Decision on HKSAR Passport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
 Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa today
welcomed the Indian government's decision to grant HKSAR passport
holders the same visa-free access as holders of British National
(Overseas) documents.
</P>
<P>
"The Indian government's decision to recognize HKSAR passports
in the same light as BN(O) after July 1 is most welcome," said the
 Chief Executive.
</P>
<P>
"This indicates the Indian government's continued confidence in
 Hong Kong," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly thirty countries have announced that they will give
visa-free access to HKSAR passport holders after July 1, when
China resumes its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong. 
</P>
