<HEADLINE> Share Prices Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices remained almost
unchanged in dull trading on Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index fell marginally by 0.56 point to
close at 1,990.12 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume declined to 98.99 million units, valued
at 254.94 million Singapore dollars (about 178.28 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 155 to 128, while 342 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
HuanHsin was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 6.44 million units. It was followed by Uraco which had
5.11 million shares traded. The Hong Kong Land was next with 5.1
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
JMH 400 top the gainers' list as it rose by 30 cents to finish
at 7.45 US dollars. Inchcape and MISC Foreign increased by 20
cents each to end at 5.2 and 3.54 Singapore dollars respectively.
Local transportation firm Tibs warrant closed 16 cents higher at
0.66 Singapore dollar.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Malaya Banking was the biggest loser as it
declined by 90 cents to end at 14.6 Singapore dollars. Creative 50
and NBT fell by 70 cents each to close at 21.6 and 19.3 Singapore
dollars respectively. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign
finished 50 cents lower at 27.8 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
