building site in Enugu City, capital of the state, when the
incident occurred at around 2:00 pm
</P>
<P>
No fewer than 30 hawkers were also reportedly taking shelter
under the building from the rain.
</P>
<P>
Some of the victims were soon rescued from the debris and rushed to
nearby hospitals by volunteers.
</P>
<P>
The Administrator of Enugu State, Colonel Sule Ahman, arrived at
the site later in the afternoon to beef up the rescue work, reports
said. 
