<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, China to Further Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev told Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian today that
Kazakhstan is confident that relations with China will be further
developed.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said there is not any obstacle in the development of
relations between the two countries, adding that their relations
have developed comprehensively and smoothly since the two
countries established diplomatic ties in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The frequent exchange of high-level visits between the two
countries has set up a solid foundation for the long-term
bilateral relationship, he said.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said the Kazakhstan-China borders are peaceful since
the four CIS (Commonwealth of Independent States) nations,
including Kazakhstan, and China signed an agreement on
strengthening mutual trust in the military field on the borders
last year as well as an accord on arms reduction on the borders
this year.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Kazakhstan has been always supporting the
territorial integrity and unity of China and opposing any
activities harmful to Chinese sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
He praised China's defense policy which insists on non-military
alliance and is devoted to strengthening its own defense, saying
that Kazakhstan would improve military cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The kazakh president said, "the return of Hong Kong to China on
July 1 is an event of great historic significance. We will share
the joy with the Chinese people," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the convening of the 15th National Congress of the Chinese
Communist Party this autumn, he said he wished the Chinese people
greater achievements in their modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who arrived here Wednesday at the head of a military
delegation on a six-day visit, said he hoped that his visit would
help strengthen cooperation between the two countries in all fields.
</P>
<P>
He said China adopts a peaceful, independent foreign policy and
will never seek military alliance, external expansion or
establishment of military bases on any other countries.
</P>
<P>
he said the friendly cooperation between China and Kazakhstan
would be in line with the interests of the two peoples and
conducive to peace and stability in the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Chi also held talks today with Kazakh Prime Minister Akezhan
Kazhegeletin on economic ties between the two countries. 
</P>
