<HEADLINE> China to Sponsor IVSC Annual Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1999 meeting of the
International Valuation Standards Committee (IVSC) will be held in
China.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be sponsored by the China Appraisal Society
(CAS), which joined the IVSC in 1995, according to an announcement
which was made public Thursday on the last day of a three-day
symposium on international appraisal standards.
</P>
<P>
IVSC, a London-headquartered self-discipline organization in
the asset evaluation industry, was founded in 1981. It now has 45
member countries.
</P>
<P>
Pan Yue, deputy director-general of China's State
Administration of State Property, said that asset evaluation has
developed rapidly in China in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that there were 3,343 approved asset
appraisal agencies and more than 55,000 professional valuers in
China at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
More than 44,300 asset evaluations were carried out in China in
1996, with the book value of assets and appraised values reaching
569.4 billion yuan and 770 billion yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
IVSC Chairman Philippe Malaquin highly commended CAS,
describing it as an important organization for setting asset
evaluation standards in China.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, jointly organized by CAS, the United Nations
Development Program and China International Economic and Technical
Exchange Center of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
cooperation, attracted industry officials and experts from China,
the United States, France, Australia, Denmark, Hong Kong and other
countries and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
