supports China's stand on most of international issues.
</P>
<P>
Chand also said that the Nepalese people are glad to see Hong
Kong's return to China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
A Nepali delegation led by its foreign minister will take part
in the handover ceremony in Hong Kong, said Chand, adding that he
himself will attend the celebrations to be held here on Hong
Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Chand proposed that a mechanism of regular
meetings be established between border officials of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Gen. Liao Xilong, head of the Chinese PLA delegation,
conveyed cordial regards to Chand from Chinese Premier Li Peng and
Defense Minister Chi Haotian.
</P>
<P>
Liao said the delegation's visit aimed to promote understanding
and deepen friendship between the two countries and the two armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived here Thursday for a five-day
visit to Nepal at the invitation of the Royal Nepalese Army.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to Nepal by a high-level Chinese
military delegation.  
