<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Marine Cable Ground Station to Be Built in Shantou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a ground station
for two international marine cables is expected to be launched
shortly in Shantou, a port city of south China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the construction will be completed
by the end of this year, and the ground station will go into
operation in early next year.
</P>
<P>
The ground station is one of the two ground stations scheduled
to be built in China for the Eurasian International Marine Cable
and Sino-American International Cable. The other ground station
will be built in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The investment for the two optical cables, the largest of their
kind in the world, will reach a total of some 2.5 billion
U.S. dollars. When completed, the two cable systems will be able
to transmit simultaneously 1.2 million digital lines and will
become an international information highway as the cables traverse
a vast number of countries and are the world's best equipped
marine systems.
</P>
<P>
China will bear more than 40 million U.S. dollars of the
investment required to lay the marine cables. The ground station
in Shantou will cover an area of more than 2.67 hectares, with a
construction space of 40 million sq m. Its total investment is
expected to reach some 100 million yuan (12 million US Dollars).
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
