<HEADLINE> Pakistan Proposes Intra-Afghan Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has proposed to host an
intra-Afghan meeting in Islamabad under the U.N. auspices, a
Foreign Office spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Apart from all the Afghan warring factions, the meeting will
also be attended by countries sharing land border with Afghanistan
as well as Russia and the United States, the spokesman told a news
briefing.
</P>
<P>
"It is our conviction that a solution to the Afghan problem has
to emerge from the Afghans themselves," he said. "The Afghans
would not accept any solution imposed on them from outside."
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan is sounding out the Afghan groups and is in touch
with the neighboring counties about the proposed meeting," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Decisions made at the intra-Afghan meeting could be guaranteed
by the U.S. and Russia to provide funds for the reconstruction of
Afghanistan as an incentive for the Afghan leaders to implement
the decisions which themselves have reached, he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that such an intra-Afghan dialogue will provide
a useful forum for the Afghan leaders to achieve national
reconciliation for the establishment of a government in which all
ethnic groups are represented," the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
