<HEADLINE> China Telecom To Enter Capital Market In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom under the Ministry
of Posts and Telecommunications is moving to list its Hong Kong
branch on the stock market there, a move which may make the
enterprise into the biggest red chip stock in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
China Business Times has reported that the listing, following
the acquisition of a 5.5 percent stake of China Telecom (Hong
Kong) in Hong Kong Telecom from its British parent Cable and
Wireless, will serve as a conduit for the opening-up of the
Chinese telecom business.
</P>
<P>
Company officials say the company plans to finish public
offering and listing of its shares this year. The US-based Goldman
Sach and China International Capital Corporation (CICC) will be
the global coordinator and lead underwriter respectively.
</P>
<P>
A leading telecom giant in the Asia Pacific region, the world's
most rapidly-growing market, China Telecom has increased its
switching capacity to 93 million telephone lines, boasting 62
million phone subscribers nationwide, including 6.85 million
mobile users. Tax revenues paid in to state coffers in 1996 by
China Telecom exceeded 100 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
