<HEADLINE> Chinese PLA Chief of General Staff Meets Australian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Advancing the long-term and stable
friendship and relations of cooperation between China and
Australia and their armed forces not only accords with the basic
interests of the people of the two countries, but also is
beneficial to safeguarding peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific
region, a senior general of the Chinese People's Liberation Army
(PLA) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the PLA General Staff Fu Quanyou made the remark
while meeting with Deputy Chief of Australia's Defense
Forces Chris Barrie.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China and Australia are two influential nations in
the region, and share common interests in a variety of areas.
</P>
<P>
He noted that through joint efforts, bilateral ties have
developed well in general since the establishment of diplomatic
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the armed forces of the two countries
constitute an important part of the two countries' ties, he said,
adding that the development of the relations between the two armed
forces should conform to that of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The PLA values its exchanges and cooperation with the
Australian Defense Forces, he said, adding that "there exist a
solid foundation and broad prospects for the cooperation between
the two countries and their armed forces."
</P>
<P>
Fu also expressed his appreciation for the Australian
government's adherence to its "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Barrie said that maintaining peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region is beneficial to the economic expansion of
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
He noted that dialogues between the two armed forces will help
deepen mutual understanding and exchanges. He also briefed Fu on
Australia's defense reform.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chief of the PLA General Staff Xiong Guangkai held
official talks with Barrie yesterday morning. Both sides exchanged
views on the relationship between the two armied forces and the
regional security of common concern. Both held that high-level
dialogues and contacts between the two armed forces are beneficial
to enhancing mutual understanding and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Barrie and his party are here on a working visit to China at
the invitation of the Headquarters of the PLA General
Staff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
