<HEADLINE> Germany Aids Afforestation in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The German government will provide
12 million marks in aid to southwest China's Sichuan Province for
a forest project on the upper reaches of the Jialing River.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with an agreement signed by the German government
and the Sichuan provincial government, the money, the largest
amount received by the local forestry departments, will be used
primarily to improve the ecological environment in Guangyuan City,
located on the upper reaches of the Jialing River,
</P>
<P>
With a low forest coverage, the city has suffered from soil
erosion for a long time.
</P>
<P>
The Jialing River, 1,120 km long and with 160,000 sq km of a
basin area, is the most important tributary of the Yangtze River
on the River's upper reaches.
</P>
<P>
According to the Provincial Department of Forestry, over the
next five years, trees will be planted on 32,000 hectare of
mountainous sides in Guangyuan with the funds from the German
government.
</P>
<P>
Upon the completion of the afforestation project, the forest
coverage in the region will surge from 27 percent to 60.3
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
