<HEADLINE> Foreign direct Investment Falls in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) in
Bangladesh fell drastically during the current fiscal year with
the total inflow recorded at only 329 million U.S. dollars,
according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The total inflow of FDI was 1.516 billion dollars in 1995-96,
729.4 million dollars in 1994-95 and 84.2 million dollars in
1993-94, said an official economy report published today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total FDI Bangladesh received during the current fiscal
year, 111 million dollars was invested in service-related
industry, 53 million dollars in textile industry, 33 million
dollars in glass, ceramic and other non-metal industry, 17 million
dollars each in food and engineering sectors.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 9 million dollars was invested in printing and
publication sector, 6 million dollars in agro-based industry, 4
million dollars in leather and rubber industry and 19 million
dollars in other industrial sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
