<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landlocked Enterprise Woos Investors From Afar (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- People often regret, especially
about what they have done hesitantly.
</P>
<P>
But Chen Yongben from Taiwan was all smiles when recalling his
wavering decision six years ago to initiate an investment in
Dulaying, a col miles away from Guiyang, the capital city of
southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
"It demands real gut to set up joint ventures in this
mountain-surrounding area, but the result proved to be much better
than in coastal areas, " said the president of Taiwan Xuya Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Though only slightly interested in its Guizhou partner's
advantages on equipment, transportation and bamboo resources at
first, the Taiwan company increased its investment three months
later, immediately after the landlocked enterprise produced
quality samples. Today the venture has risen into the most
profitable investment of Xuya Group in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the booming economic development zones appealing for
foreign investors, the col, known as Dulaying, attracted no
foreign investment until six years ago.
</P>
<P>
But since then, overseas fund has been flocking there by the
day from the United States, France, Australia, Hong Kong and
Taiwan, making it a rising star in southwestern Guizhou province.
</P>
<P>
And there are already 14 joint ventures for the present, all of
them having a same partner -- Guiyang Freight Car Works.
</P>
<P>
Although moved to landlocked areas in inland Guizhou province
in a national strategy of industrial relocation to prepare for
major wars in 1960s, the freight car producer under the Ministry
of Railways still holds strong appeal to foreign capital due to
its great advantages on talents, technology, equipment and
management.
</P>
<P>
Actually, Guiyang Freight Car Works is not the only one of such
relocated old industrial firms which came out to be hot spots for
foreign capital after the opening-up drive was adopted.
</P>
<P>
Experts agree that infrastructure in Dulaying counts heavily in
luring more overseas funds. Besides a sufficient supply of water
and electrical power, the area also has convenient access to railway
transportation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970613.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landlocked Enterprise Woos Investors From Afar (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manager from the US partner of the Sino-American Universal Wire
Rope Co. Ltd said he was deeply impressed with the outstanding
management expertise in the enterprise, which turned a
money-losing enterprise into profit-making and had its products
exported worldwide.
</P>
<P>
All the employees of these joint ventures originally worked in
the Guiyang Freight Car Works.
</P>
<P>
"They are just as good as workers in Shanghai," said Eric
Gravell, executive vice president of the American Pacific
Aviation &AMP; Technology Corp, a co-sponsor.
</P>
