<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Joint Communique of PRC and Republic of Macedonia Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Joint Communique of the
People's Republic of China (PRC) and the Republic of Macedonia was
released here today. Its full text is as follows:
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of His Excellency Jiang Zemin, president of
the People's Republic of China, His Excellency Kiro Gligorov,
president of the Republic of Macedonia, paid a state visit to the
People's Republic of China from June 9 to 13, 1997.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin of the People's Republic of China and
President Kiro Gligorov of the Republic of Macedonia held
talks. The two leaders had an in-depth exchange of views on ways
of bolstering bilateral relations and international issues of
mutual interest and reached broad consensus, The talks proceeded
in a sincere and friendly atmosphere. Both sides were satisfied
with the outcome of the talks, and of the view that the visit
would have an important impact on the continued development of
China-Macedonia friendly relations and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China and Macedonia have been friendly towards each other and
the two peoples enjoyed a traditional friendship. The two sides
expressed satisfaction with their cooperation in the political,
economic, cultural and educational fields since the establishment
of diplomatic relations, and they shared the view that the
long-term, stable and all-round development of their friendly
relations and cooperation conform to the common aspirations of the
two peoples, serves the fundamental interests of both countries
and is also conducive to peace and development in Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are determined to intensify their bilateral
cooperation on the principled basis of equality and mutual benefit
in all fields, particularly in the economic relations and
trade. They will encourage their respective companies, enterprises
adn localities to increase contact, enhance mutual understanding
and conduct multi-channeled and multi-formed cooperation with a
view to promoting the long-term and steady development of the
bilateral economic relations and trade.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian side reaffirmed its continued commitment to the
principled "one China" position recognizing that there is but one
China in the world and Taiwan is an inalienable part of China and
that the Government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate government representing the entire Chinese people. The
Republic of Macedonia has undertaken not to enter into official
relations or engage in any official contacts with Taiwan. The
Macedonian side stated that it valued China's important role in
Asia and the international community at large, spoke highly of the
independent foreign policy of peace pursued by China and
appreciated the achievements it had made in its reform and opening
up endeavor.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side affirmed that it would respect the
independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of Macedonia
and the road to development chosen by the Macedonian people. It
admired the achievements made by Macedonia in developing its
economy and improving the living standards of its people, spoke
highly of the foreign policy of peace pursued by Macedonia and its
positive efforts in stabilizing the situation in the Balkan region
and expressed its understanding of Macedonia's endeavor to join in
the process of European intergration.
</P>
<P>
President of the republic of Macedonia Kiro Gligorov thanked
the Chinese side for its warm reception and generous hospitality,
and invited President Jiang Zemin of the People's Republic of
China to visit Macedonia at his convenience. President Jiang Zemin
expressed his thanks and accepted the invitation with pleasure.
</P>
<P>
President of the People's  President of the Republic
</P>
<P>
Republic of China  Macedonia
</P>
<P>
 Jiang Zemin  Kiro Gligorov
</P>
<P>
Beijing, 9 June 1997



nnnn
</P>
