<HEADLINE> Polish Navy to Enhance Links With NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Polish Navy will work with its
counterparts from Germany and Denmark in training, war games and
personnel exchange programs.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation is provided by agreements signed by the Polish
Navy separately with German and Danish navies at Polish port
Gdynia today, Polish Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two agreements is another sign of Poland's edging closer
toward the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), a senior
Polish Defense Ministry official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Days before signing the documents, the Polish Navy joined
forces from 12 other countries, including Britain, the United
States, Denmark and Germany, in an exercise in the Baltic Sea.
</P>
<P>
A total of 45 vessels and 7,500 seamen took part in the war
game. 
</P>
