<HEADLINE> Russia to Cut Armed Forces' Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The Russian armed services are to
be cut from five to three forces by 2005 as part of the
fundamental restructuring of the military announced by President
Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev made the announcement
today during a visit to Russia's Black Sea Fleet based in
Sevastopol. But he gave no further details, the InterFax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Russian military experts say the plan involves merging the
Ground Forces and the Navy into "the General Purpose Forces", the
Air Force and the Air Defense Force into "the Air Defense
Forces", the nuclear forces of the Air Force and the Air Defense
Force and the Strategic Rocket Force into "the Rocket Space
Forces." 
</P>
</TEXT>
