<HEADLINE> Oil Consumption Up 2 Percent in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Oil consumption in Thailand rose 2
percent in the first five months of this year compared with the
same period of last year, averaging 731,999 barrels per day (bpd),
according to the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
During the period, diesel oil consumption grew 6 percent to
average 324,261 bpd, accounting for nearly 45 percent of the total
consumption, said a report released recently by the Commercial
Registration Department under the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Gas consumption went up 7 percent to average 127,382 bpd,
accounting for 17.4 percent of the total while aviation fuel
consumed averaged 63,416 bpd, up 6 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, ordinary fuel oil consumption around the country
declined by 11 percent to 158,969 bpd, including 78,819 bpd used
by the Electricity Generating Authority of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Kerosene consumption continued to drop by 11 percent to 1,583
bpd.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
