<P>
"In future we will attempt to provide the type of projects that
would promote self-employment and training for self-employment,"
the release quoted President Chandrika Kumaratunga as saying here
Thursday evening while addressing representatives of donor
countries, agencies and implementing authorities.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure projects such as minor roads and small
irrigation works would also be one of the prime aspects to be
implemented under the new rural economic development plan, she
said.
</P>
<P>
The country first launched an Integrated Rural Development
Program in 1978 and the program is still being implemented in 15
districts at an annual cost of 20.6 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The president said the program will be re-oriented in keeping
with the new focus, according to the release.
</P>
<P>
It quoted the president as saying that during the past many
years successive governments implemented many welfare schemes such
as free food, free health services and free education.
</P>
<P>
These had helped create a comparatively highly educated and
healthy society but one that was economically poor, she said,
noting that in view of the present needs, there is no alternative
but to re-orientate development programs toward income-generating
schemes for sustainable development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
