<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Japan to Cooperate in Insurance Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese insurance company has
signed a memorandum of understanding with Myanmar to cooperate in
the insurance business in the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the memorandum signed here Thursday, Japan's Yasuda Fire
and Marine Insurance Company and the state-owned Myanmar Insurance
will set up an insurance joint venture in Myanmar, the official
paper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Yasuda is one of the two Japanese insurance companies which
opened representative offices in Myanmar in January last year. The
other one is Mitsui.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar enacted the Insurance Business Law in June last year,
permitting local and private companies and those with foreign
investment to undertake insurance businesses in the country.
</P>
