<HEADLINE> Cuban Steel Output Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's steel output rose 36 percent
to 137,200 tons in the first five months of the year over the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Based on this figure, the authorities predicted today that the
steel output for the year will be 35 percent higher than the
target of 330,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Rising production has been accompanied by lower spending per
ton on raw materials, electricity and fuel.
</P>
<P>
Cuba's steel output has been increasing steadily over the last
few years to make up for the loss of imports from countries of the
former Soviet Union, once the island's main trading partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
