<HEADLINE> U.S. Won't Issue Wild Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- American Track and Field's
executive committee would not change the American selection
process for the world championships team by issuing "wild card"
entries to any U.S. stars.
</P>
<P>
The decision, made by the committee on Thursday, means that
double Olympic gold medalist Michael Johnson will also not be
given the "wild card".
</P>
<P>
But U.S. track officials said it would welcome the IAAF
inviting all 1995 world champions to defend their titles in Athens
in August. That would include Johnson, decathlete Dan O'Brien and
women's sprinter Gwen Torrence, who are all missing this week's
national meet in Indianapolis because of injuries. 
