<HEADLINE> Microwave Oven Joint Venture Operational in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A major microwave joint venture
recently went operational in Shenzhen, one of China's special
economic zones in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Jointly financed by a local microwave oven producer, a Hong
Kong investment company and a Japanese corporation with 120
million yuan, the designed production capacity of the joint
venture is 600,000 ovens a year.
</P>
<P>
The venture will produce 20 varieties of ovens, of which 70
percent will be for export.
</P>
<P>
A recent market survey indicated that the total sales of
microwave ovens last year hit 2.3 million units. A local expert
predicted that the market demand this year might top 3.5
million units.  
</P>
